cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper discusses a technique for reducing the size and computational work of DNNs, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves optimization and feature selection, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
